U.S. Census data is available for both the Reinholds census-designated place (CDP)<ref name="CDP stats">{{cite web |title=Reinholds CDP, Pennsylvania |url=https://www.census.gov |website=[[United States Census Bureau]] |publisher=U.S. Census Bureau |access-date=3 February 2019 }} Search for "Reinholds CDP, Pennsylvania"</ref> and the larger area covered by the Reinholds ZIP code, 17569.<ref name="ZIP stats">{{cite web |title=17589 |url=https://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/cf/1.0/en/zip/17569/ALL |archive-url=https://archive.today/20200213004311/https://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/cf/1.0/en/zip/17569/ALL |url-status=dead |archive-date=13 February 2020 |website=American Fact Finder |publisher=U.S. Census Bureau |access-date=3 February 2019 }}</ref>

The Reinholds CDP has a 2017 estimated population of 1,849 with a median age of 37.7 and a median household income of $77,107 for 629 housing units. Individuals below the poverty level include 15.3% of the population; 91.1% of the population had attained a high school diploma or a higher level of education. The population includes 1,743 "white" individuals (94.3%) and 106 "American Indian and Alaska Native" individuals (5.7%).<ref name="CDP stats"/>

The 17569 ZIP code covers {{convert|16.36|sqmi|km2|abbr=on}} including Reinholds plus the areas of [[Blainsport, Pennsylvania|Blainsport]], [[Swartzville, Pennsylvania|Swartzville]], and Vera Cruz in Lancaster County, as well as [[Vinemont, Pennsylvania|Vinemont]] in [[Berks County, Pennsylvania|Berks County]].<ref name="ZIP">{{cite web |title=17569 |url=https://www.unitedstateszipcodes.org/17569/ |website=United States ZIP Codes.org |access-date=3 February 2019}}</ref> The ZIP code had a 2017 estimated population of 5,837 with a median age of 36.2 and a median household income of $79,375 for 1,981 housing units. Individuals below the poverty level include 5.2% of the population; 83.5% of the population had attained a high school diploma or a higher level of education. The population includes 5,559 "white" individuals (95.2%), 136 "Asian" (2.3%), 106 "American Indian and Alaska Native"(1.8%), 36 of two or more races (0.6%), and 124 Hispanic or Latino (of any race) (2.1%).<ref name="CDP stats"/>

